<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,1079]" box="[151,282,151,176]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,1079]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,188,213]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Male</emphasis>
(n = 4, except when otherwise stated). Total length 2.85–2.98, 
<quantity box="[991,1096,188,213]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.91" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="2.91">2.91 mm</quantity>
. Wing length 1.38–1.47, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.43" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="1.43">1.43 mm</quantity>
. Total length / wing length 2.03–2.07, 2.04. Wing length / length of profemur 1.67–1.73, 1.71.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,1079]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis box="[199,329,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Coloration.</emphasis>
Head and thorax stramineous; abdomen pale, with narrow, brown anterior transverse bands on tergites II–VIII. Legs stramineous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,1079]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis box="[199,260,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[276,362,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–34" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1883,1905]" captionTargetBox="[253,1320,216,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-64@26.[226,1360,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 30–34. Beardius bucephalus sp. n., male. 30—head; 31—thorax; 32—wing; 33—anal point and tergite IX and dorsal aspect of left gonocoxite and gonostylus; 34—hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5270906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5270906/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
). AR 1.36–1.47 (2), ultimate flagellomere 561–589 (2) µm long. Temporal setae 9–12, 11; not well separated in inner and outer verticals and postorbitals. Clypeus with 10–14, 12 setae. Tentorium 114–127, 121 µm long; 30–33, 31 µm wide. Stipes 121–139, 134 µm long. Palpomere lengths (in µm): 30–43, 35; 30–35, 33; 124–137, 129; 149–159, 156; 230–248 (3). Third palpomere with 2–3, 3 sensillae subapically, longest 13–20, 15 µm long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,1079]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis box="[199,280,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[300,388,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–34" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1883,1905]" captionTargetBox="[253,1320,216,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-64@26.[226,1360,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 30–34. Beardius bucephalus sp. n., male. 30—head; 31—thorax; 32—wing; 33—anal point and tergite IX and dorsal aspect of left gonocoxite and gonostylus; 34—hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5270906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5270906/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
). Scutal tubercle present. Antepronotum without setae. Dorsocentrals 6–7, 7; acrostichals absent; prealars 2. Scutellum with 4 setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,1079]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis box="[199,257,584,607]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[272,357,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–34" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1883,1905]" captionTargetBox="[253,1320,216,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-64@26.[226,1360,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 30–34. Beardius bucephalus sp. n., male. 30—head; 31—thorax; 32—wing; 33—anal point and tergite IX and dorsal aspect of left gonocoxite and gonostylus; 34—hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5270906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5270906/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
). VR 1.24–1.35, 1.30. R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[632,656,598,612]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">4+5</subScript>
with 1–2, 2 setae at apex. Brachiolum with 2 setae. Remaining veins bare.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,1079]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis box="[199,259,659,682]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Legs.</emphasis>
Spur of fore tibia (including scale) 43–48, 45 µm long; spur of mid tibia (including comb) 70–80, 75 µm long; spur of hind tibia (including comb) 75–86, 80 µm long. Width at apex of fore tibia 48–59, 54 µm; of mid tibia 51–56, 54 µm; of hind tibia 54–59, 56 µm. Lengths and proportions of legs as in 
<tableCitation box="[1057,1142,730,755]" captionStart="TABLE 5" captionStartId="25.[151,241,1344,1367]" captionText="TABLE 5. Lengths (in µm) and proportions of legs of Beardius bucephalus sp. n., male (n = 1–4)." pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Table 5</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,1079]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis box="[199,342,768,791]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Hypopygium</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[361,497,766,791]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–34" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1883,1905]" captionTargetBox="[253,1320,216,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-64@26.[226,1360,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 30–34. Beardius bucephalus sp. n., male. 30—head; 31—thorax; 32—wing; 33—anal point and tergite IX and dorsal aspect of left gonocoxite and gonostylus; 34—hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5270906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5270906/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Figs 33–34</figureCitation>
). Anal point bluntly triangular, 8–18, 13 µm long; sitting on rounded, posterior protrusion of tergite IX. Tergite IX without setae, tergal bands absent. Laterosternite IX with 2 setae. Phallapodeme 51–68, 58 µm long. Transverse sternapodeme 40–46, 43 µm long. Gonocoxite 91–114, 106 µm long. Superior volsella digitiform, curved, 61–68, 66 µm long, with 5–9, 7 dorsal, and 4–5, 4 ventral setae, without microtrichia. Median volsella with 1–4, 3 setae, longest 15–25, 20 µm long. Inferior volsella clavate, slightly curved, 89–101, 94 µm long, with 2 apical thin setae and 6–9, 8 stout setae subapically; projection subrectangular, 38–43, 40 µm long, arising from base of volsella. Gonostylus 139–154, 147 µm long. HR 0.65–0.75, 0.72. HV 2.09–2.22, 2.15.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,1079]" box="[199,606,1018,1043]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,481,1018,1043]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Female and immatures.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
